=== BLE-on-NUCLEO end-to-end validation — v0.10.1 ===
Date:     2026-05-29
Board:    NUCLEO-L476RG + X-NUCLEO-IDB05A1 BLE shield + INA219 @ 0x40
Firmware: app/boards/nucleo_l476rg_ble_current.conf
          (BLE transport + INA219 current sense + coulomb counting)
Gateway:  ibattery-gateway run  (bleak on macOS, run from iTerm)
Stack:    InfluxDB 2.9.1 + Grafana 13.0.1 (cloud/docker-compose.yml)

This is the first time v3 (32-byte) telemetry has traversed BLE on any
platform. It validates three fixes shipped together:
  1. Firmware BLE MTU: CONFIG_BT_L2CAP_TX_MTU 27 -> 35 (ACL 31 -> 39).
     ATT_MTU 27 capped notification payloads at 24 bytes, so 32-byte v3
     packets were silently dropped/truncated. They never went over BLE.
  2. Gateway device matching: name-only match was unreliable on macOS
     (CoreBluetooth populates device.name asynchronously). Now matches on
     the advertised service UUID via find_device_by_filter (per-packet).
  3. Firmware re-advertise: on_disconnect restarted advertising inline,
     racing controller teardown and silently failing -> device vanished
     until reboot. Now deferred to the system workqueue.

